<Author>venturagm
<Content>Avoid during the summer This 4 year old property has some impressive finishes and views, however, the hotel has started having major A/C issues.Random rooms thoughout the building started losing their A/C and they became veritable ovens. Even the Executive rooms and the Executive lounge have suffered. It was so warm in the Executive lounge one night that folks refused to stay inside the lounge and opted for the terrace spaces. Hotel staff privately explained that the hotel has been experiencing the mechanical failures for the last 8 months with growing severity. Some rooms continue to provide A/C, but it is now more likely that your A/C will not work. Management/Director claim that the issue has been addressed, but the staff contends that nothing has been done and the situation is getting worse. I can personally vouch for the continued mechanical lapses.We had to leave our room door open to allow the A/C from the hallway to help cool our room (and this was the second room we had been moved to). The third room on our final night provided moderate A/C. Compared to the first two ovens, it was a welcome change. All three rooms were Executive level rooms.Given the extremely warm temperatures that can affect Florence, I would avoid this property during the summer. The poor A/C put a real damper on our enthusiasm for the visit, and prevented us from getting any real sleep. By the third day, we were tired, hot, sticky and resigned to a poor hotel experience in Florence. I can't understand how Hilton would allow one of their properties to get this bad.Maid service is here isn't very accomodating. They slam doors and create a thunderstorm of noise in the mornings while cleaning vacated rooms. Even the sound proof door feature couldn't filter them out.The location isn't ideal if you travel by train or plan to spend a lot of time in Florence proper. The limited shuttle runs to the train station mitigate this issue to a degree, however there is a 3 hour lapse during the day (noon to 3pm) and then the shuttle stops at 8pm. Taxi rides back to the hotel from downtown run about 20 Euros.If you go during cooler months, you'll be able to enjoy some nice views from the higher floors. The Executive Lounge terrace can provide some stunning views and romantic sunsets. This hotel has so much potential. I can't tell you how sad I was to deal with the sub-par mechanical systems. No matter how stunning a hotel is, you cannot ignore the basics, especially COMFORT. 
