<Author>MichWorldTraveler
<Content>Awesome Staff, Great Hotel! The second stop on our honeymoon...Despite telling every hotel we were going to that we were on our honeymoon, this was the only hotel that actually did anything nice for us...They had a chilled bottle of champagne waiting for us in the room when we arrived! That was just the beginning of the great service! Front desk staff was friendly, helpful and took the time to answer every question we had and suggested a strategy for seeing Florence.Yes, the hotel is outside of the city center, but the shuttle runs hourly--on top of that, you can reserve a seat on any shuttle you want. The shuttle drops you right at the main train station, in the thick of the city...Just hop in a cab from there to get to the Uffizi, Accademia or walk to many of the other nearby sights. Someone below mentions the hotel being near a bowling alley (and a cinema too)--it was, but I don't really see how that detracted from the hotel in the slightest--it's not like we heard pins falling--we wouldn't have even known it was there if we hadn't passed it on the shuttle on the way to the city center.We were given an executive floor room (Hilton Gold). The executive lounge staff was very friendly, and kept the bar well-stocked as well as the munchies in the evening and the breakfast items in the morning. We found ourselves hanging out there every night when we got back to the room, having cocktails and enjoying the 360 degree view of Florence and the Tuscan region.The room was modern, albeit small, even by European standards...But it was sufficient for the two of us. The bed was comfortable and the bathroom was nice.The restaurant was one of the better hotel restaurants I've eaten at...For a hotel it was reasonably priced, and they catered quite well to my bride who has gluten allergies. 
